pageContext.claim: “We made a big deal with Saudi Arabia and Russia and saving 10 million barrels a day each and that knocked it out and now you're back to about $41 a barrel and we worked hard on it because it looked really bleak about three months ago when this pandemic started for the oil and gas and now it's looking really good were here really almost celebrating in a sense.”
pageContext.analysis: Oil prices are still roughly half what they were at the beginning of 2020. Analysts have warned a coronavirus resurgence could add more instability to the market.
